C-structures: deque

deque_initiate: -> returns a pointer for a empty deque structure, upon initializing the size of the elements
that will be pushed in deque must be offered
deque_push_back: -> pushes the element offered at the back of the deque structure offered, if the realloc for
the deque fails it will free the memory of the deque and return MEMORY_PROBLEM
deque_push_front: -> same as the push back but it will insert the element at the front of the deque
deque_pop_front: -> deletes the first element of the deque, returns EMPTY if the deque is empty
deque_pop_back: -> same as the pop front, but deletes the last element
deque_front: -> returns a pointer with the size of the elements of the deque with the value of the
element at the front of the deque or NULL if the deque is empty
deque_back: -> same as the front but offers the information for the last element
deque_free: -> frees the memory that the deque used
deque_print: -> prints the elements of the deque using the printer function offered for printing the 
individual elements of the deque